menu "Profile: Micro Embedded Device 2025 Server Profile"

menu "Facet: Embedded DataChange Subscription 2022 Server Facet"

config MUC_OPCUA_FACET_EMBEDDED_DATACHANGE_SUBSCRIPTION_2022_SERVER
	bool "Enable Embedded DataChange Subscription 2022 Server Facet"
	default y if MUC_OPCUA_INTERN_PROFILE_MICRO_EMBEDDED_DEVICE_2025_SERVER
	help
	  Implementation state: deferred.
	  OPC source: OPC-10000-7 §4.2.
	  Notes: This Facet specifies the minimum level of support for data change notifications within subscriptions. It minimizes memory and processing overhead required to implement the Facet. This Facet includes functionality to create, modify and delete Subscriptions and to add, modify and remove Monitored Items. It is recommended that Servers shall support one Subscription with up to two items for each Session. In addition, support for two parallel Publish requests is suggested. This Facet is geared for a platform such as the Nano or Micro Embedded Device Server Profiles in which memory is limited and will be managed. It supersedes the Embedded DataChange Subscription Server Facet.

# Monitor Basic (opc_cu_2963)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 2963:Monitor Basic.
#   Notes: Support the following MonitoredItem Services: CreateMonitoredItems, ModifyMonitoredItems, DeleteMonitoredItems and SetMonitoringMode.
comment "Monitor Basic (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Subscription PublishRequest Queue Overflow (opc_cu_3143)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3143:Subscription PublishRequest Queue Overflow.
#   Notes: If the maximum supported number of PublishRequests has been queued and a new PublishRequest arrives, the "oldest" PublishRequest has to be discarded by returning the proper error.
comment "Subscription PublishRequest Queue Overflow (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Base Info Fixed SamplingInterval (opc_cu_3196)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3196:Base Info Fixed SamplingInterval.
#   Notes: Exposes diagnostic information on fixed sampling intervals (SamplingIntervalDiagnosticsArray) when the Server is handling subscriptions with fixed sampling intervals and the EnabledFlag in the ServerDiagnostics Object is set to TRUE.
comment "Base Info Fixed SamplingInterval (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Subscription Basic (opc_cu_3727)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3727:Subscription Basic.
#   Notes: Support the following Subscription Services: CreateSubscription, ModifySubscription, DeleteSubscriptions, Publish, Republish and SetPublishingMode.
comment "Subscription Basic (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Base Info Server Capabilities Subscriptions (opc_cu_3911)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3911:Base Info Server Capabilities Subscriptions.
#   Notes: Exposes AggregateFunctions, MaxSubscriptions, MaxMonitoredItems, MaxSubscriptionsPerSession and MaxMonitoredItemsPerSubscription of the ServerCapabilities Object as well as MaxMonitoredItemsPerCall of the OperationLimits Object.
comment "Base Info Server Capabilities Subscriptions (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Subscription Publish Basic (opc_cu_3913)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3913:Subscription Publish Basic.
#   Notes: Support at least 2 Publish Service requests per Session.
comment "Subscription Publish Basic (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Base Info SemanticChange Bit (opc_cu_3922)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 3922:Base Info SemanticChange Bit.
#   Notes: Supports setting the SemanticsChanged Bit in the statusCode when a semantic change occurs, such as a change in the engineering unit associated with the Value Attribute.
comment "Base Info SemanticChange Bit (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Base Info Server Capabilities MaxMonitoredItemsQueueSize (opc_cu_4055)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 4055:Base Info Server Capabilities MaxMonitoredItemsQueueSize.
#   Notes: Exposes MaxMonitoredItemsQueueSize of the ServerCapabilities Object.
comment "Base Info Server Capabilities MaxMonitoredItemsQueueSize (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Monitor Items 2 (opc_cu_5207)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 5207:Monitor Items 2.
#   Notes: Support at least 2 MonitoredItems per Subscription where the size of each MonitoredItem is at least equal to size of Double.
comment "Monitor Items 2 (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

# Monitor Value Change V2 (opc_cu_5208)
#   Implementation state: unimplemented -- visible but not selectable.
#   Detail: CU 5208:Monitor Value Change V2.
#   Notes: Support creation of MonitoredItems for Attribute value changes. This includes support of the IndexRange to select a single element or a range of elements when the Attribute value is an array. This ConformanceUnit does not require queuing when multiple value changes occur during a "publish period". I.e. the latest change will be sent in the Notification.
comment "Monitor Value Change V2 (NOT IMPLEMENTED)"

